com.mobius.vdrapi
Interface IJPEGParameters

public interface IJPEGParameters

A class implements IJPEGParameters to indicate that it can render the page in JPEG format and it can use the quality factor and the passes setting while rendering the page.

Method Summary

Method Detail

setPasses

public void setPasses(int passes)
Sets the number of passes to be used while rendering the page data as progressive JPEG. A progessive JPEG file stores more than one copy of an image, each of which progessively adds a higher level of quality. For example, if this value is set to 1, the JPEG filter only loads the first scan of the image. The default value is zero.

setQualityFactor

public void setQualityFactor(int qFactor)
Sets the quality factor to be used while rendering the page as JPEG. This is the quality of compression and can be in a range of 1 - 100. The default value is 100 and provides the highest retention of original pixel values.
